meetings.title: Google  - Wesley Chun
meetings.description: Wesley Chun is a developer advocate at Google with many years of experience. Wesley will be giving a developer's overview about ML concepts and how these concepts work. He will also provide an overview of the various available Google Cloud Machine Learning API's.

meetings.title: NVIDIA - Kristopher Keipert
meetings.description: Kristopher Keipert is a Senior Solutions Architect at NVIDIA who will be giving a talk about the unique offerings that NVIDIA has to help lower the barrier to entry for AI researchers.

meetings.title: Eddy Liang
meetings.description: Eddy is a senior Computer Science student expanding on his AI capstone project.

meetings.title: Will Burrus & Lower
meetings.description: Lower is a company using AI to offer consumers better home loans. They will be talking about how they use these skills on the job.

meetings.title: TensorFlow Hub Workshop
meetings.description: We will be learning how to use pre-made tensorflow projects for fast and easy prototyping.

meetings.title: Mathworks Handwriting Recognition Workshop
meetings.description: We will be making a machine learning program which can recognize & label numbers in a dataset.

meetings.title: Video Games & AI
meetings.description: We will be talking about how to build AI in video games and discuss the best games that include AI!

meetings.title: Club Meeting #1
meetings.description: This week AI club will be running a meeting to introduce students to Artificial Intelligence.

meetings.title: ACM-W Colab Talk
meetings.description: Our president, Jack Dubbs, will be giving a presentation on using AI to do stock price prediction from daily news articles.

meetings.title: AI Club: Aware
meetings.description: Come hear Aware talk about how they use artificial intelligence to help workplace security and understand behavioral analytics!

meetings.title: AI Safety Discussion
meetings.description: The AI Club will be hosting a discussion on AI Safety. We will be talking about far and near-future scenarios, and will be watching two videos before the talk.

meetings.title: Root Insurance
meetings.description: Root's core data science challenge is understanding driving behavior from smartphone sensor data. Come and meet Dr. Matt Bonakdarpour and Dr. David Martin, the VP of Data Science and Chief Data Scientist.

meetings.title: Ghostery: Utilizing machine learning for internet privacy
meetings.description: What’s the cost of using the internet? It depends who you ask. Join us as we discuss how the internet business model works from both the consumer and professional side of things.

meetings.title: Deep Lens VIPER
meetings.description: Utilizing machine vision to match cancer patients to clinical trails.

meetings.title: AI Club Workshop #2
meetings.description: This week AI Club's advisor, professor Alan Ritter, will be presenting on his research using natural language processing to predict events through Twitter!

meetings.title: AI Club Workshop #1
meetings.description: This week AI club will be running a workshop alongside Business Builders Club to introduce members to Kaggle.

meetings.title: Natural Language Processing in Capital One's Virtual Assistant
meetings.description: Learn how Capital One uses Eno to understand how customers text about their money.

meetings.title: First Meeting

meetings.title: The Internet Knows Who You Are and We Can Prove It
meetings.description: The Ghostery team presents how they use AI to enhance security.

meetings.title: Artificial Intelligence and the Law
meetings.description: Attorney Drew Stephens presents the legal implications of AI.

meetings.description: Learn how Capital One uses Eno to understand how customers text about their money.

meetings.title: Modeling Language and Vision
meetings.description: When you try to give directions, or point out an object in a crowded scene, your brain gathers information from the visual cortex and uses it to create an effective description using language. Professor Micha Elsner will talk about how AI can help us to understand and model this process.
